item.title: Qld COVID nurse under investigation
item.description: Queensland's Chief Health Officer has warned we may never eradicate the COVID-19 virus, which is now threatening patients and staff at a nursing home in Rockhampton.

item.title: Bikie nabbed after Gold Coast chase
item.description: A Queensland bikie has been caught with a gun, drugs and almost $50,000 in cash after a high-speed chase on the Gold Coast.

item.title: Overseas students waiting on Vic support
item.description: International students in Victoria are still waiting to receive support payments promised by the state government almost a month ago.

item.title: Praise for Brazil’s embattled Bolsonaro
item.description: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro has greeted hundreds of supporters who gathered before the presidential offices to back his open-the-economy drive even as the coronavirus pandemic sweeps across the country.

item.title: Light plane crashes in regional Victoria
item.description: A light plane has crashed in regional Victoria, leaving one person with minor injuries.

item.title: NAB to query home loan customers
item.description: National Australia Bank says its customer support team is starting check-ins with customers on about 80,000 home loans who have received a repayment pause to help them through the impact of COVID-19.

item.title: NSW virus deaths hit 48, road chaos feared
item.description: A man aged in his 60s has died in NSW after contracting coronavirus from a personal contact, taking the state's death toll to 48 and nationwide toll to 99.

item.title: Qld parents slain, son arrested in NSW
item.description: A Queensland man will appear in a Sydney court accused of murdering his parents before going on a 900 kilometre road trip to Sydney.

item.title: Canadian air force jet crash kills one
item.description: A jet from the Canadian air force's Snowbirds aerobatics team that was on a tour to lift spirits during the coronavirus outbreak has crashed in British Columbia, killing a crew member and injuring another, defence officials say.

item.title: McIlroy seals millions for COVID-19 relief
item.description: Rory McIlroy has delivered the money shot as live golf returned to television in the US for a Skins game that raised more than $US5 million ($A7.8m) for coronavirus relief funds.
